mmute%20takes%20me%20about%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20my%20job%20is%20meetings%20%E2%80%94%20figuring%20out%20where%20there%20might%20be%20opportunities.%20One%20or%20two%20days%20a%20week%2C%20I%20travel%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20Korea%20to%20meet%20up%20with%20Korean%20companies%20and%20present%20the%20technologies%20my%20clients%20are%20working%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20start%20a%20new%20project%2C%20I'll%20cold-call%20people%20or%20follow%20up%20with%20those%20I%20met%20through%20exhibitions%20and%20shows.%20I'll%20tell%20them%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20remember%20me%2C%20I%20had%20this%20great%20technology.%20I%20want%20to%20come%20and%20meet%20you%20in%20person%20and%20tell%20you%20more%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20can%20get%20home%20by%206%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20I'll%20play%20with%20my%20kids%20at%20the%20playground%20or%20read%20some%20books.%20I%20try%20to%20let%20my%20wife%20have%20a%20break%2C%20because%20having%20two%20boys%20is%20really%20stressful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ab783a18-5fed-4904-b965-8a830b2790aa%5C%22%3EWhat%20I%20gave%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouth-korea-debt-10-a-day-kang-gwang-sik-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20life%20in%20Korea%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20exciting.%20I'm%20on%20TV%20every%20few%20months.%20I'm%20a%20sponsored%20biker.%20I%20give%20lectures%20at%20universities%20on%20the%20side.%20That%20wouldn't%20happen%20in%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20I%20would%20just%20be%20some%20dude.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20stayed%20in%20the%20US%2C%20my%20career%20probably%20would%20have%20progressed%20faster%2C%20and%20I'd%20be%20making%20more%20money.%20In%20Korea%2C%20promotions%20can%20take%20longer%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20you're%20waiting%20for%20someone%20above%20you%20to%20retire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESalaries%20are%20generally%20lower%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Korea%2C%20I%20make%20a%20little%20less%20money%2C%20in%20exchang