3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222073%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20orange%20cat%20sits%20inside%20a%20large%20cardboard%20box%20looking%20content.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63333bbf488b340019deb7ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221555%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBoxes%20can%20make%20your%20cat%20feel%20safe%20and%20comforted.%3Cp%3ECrystal%20Raypole%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBoxes%20offer%20cats%20a%20quiet%20space%20for%20a%20good%20snooze%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20vantage%20point%20for%20hunting%20prey.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20dark%20safety%20of%20a%20box%20can%20also%20reduce%20stress%2C%20while%20cardboard%20offers%20a%20great%20texture%20to%20scratch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20your%20cat%20spends%20more%20time%20hiding%20and%20won't%20leave%20the%20box%20to%20eat%2C%20contact%20your%20vet%20right%20away.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20just%20bought%20your%20furry%20feline%20friend%20a%20bunch%20of%20brand-new%20toys%2C%20but%20they've%20ignored%20them%20all%20in%20favor%20of%20that%20boring%20cardboard%20box%20you%20tossed%20into%20the%20corner%20last%20week.%20What's%20the%20deal%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDon't%20worry%20%E2%80%94%20your%20cat%20is%20just%20being%20a%20cat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20cats%20like%20to%20hide%20in%20dark%2C%20cozy%20places.%20But%20boxes%20offer%20your%20cat%20more%20than%20a%20quiet%20space%20to%20curl%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERead%20on%20for%20five%20reasons%20why%20your%20cat%20would%20rather%20slink%20into%20a%20box%20than%20play%20with%20those%20fancy%20new%20toys%2C%20along%20with%20some%20tips%20to%20engage%20their%20natural%20instincts%20during%20playtime.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d14c6663-76ec-43e2-b2d3-cd44519d42fc%5C%22%3E1.%20They%20can%20make%20your%20cat%20more%20comfortable%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20dark%20spots%2C%20even%20the%20inside%20of%20a%20plain%20old%20cardboard%20box%2C%20can%20bring%20comfort%20to%20cats%20%E2%80%94%20but%20not%20entirely%20for%20the%20reasons%20you%20might%20think.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20cats%2C%20from%20domesticated%20house%20cats%20to%20their%20larger%2C%20more%20ferocious%20feline%20cousins%2C%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbesjournals.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1002%2Fpan3.6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enatural%20predators%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoxes%20and%20other%20hiding%20spots%20provide%20a%20vantage%20point%20for%20better%20situational%20awareness%2C%20an%20essential%20asset%20for%20predators%20hunting%20prey.%20In%20short%2C%20a%20box%20helps%20your%20cat%20stay%20concealed%20while%20they%20monitor%20that%20spider%2C%20toy%20mouse%2C%20or%20flashing%20red%20dot%20that%20keeps%20darting%20across%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20actually%20more%20comforted%20by%20being%20in%20dark%20locations%20where%20they%20can%20see%20the%20things%20that%20are%20around%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aaha.org%2Fpractice-resources%2Fcentral-line-the-aaha-podcast%2Fguest-bios%2Fdr.-cherice-roth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Cherice%20Roth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20chief%20veterinary%20officer%20at%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffuzzy.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFuzzy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20online%20platform%20that%20remotely%20connects%20pet%20owners%20with%20veterinarians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20animals%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20food%20chain%2C%20like%20cats%2C%20find%20comfort%20in%20having%20awareness%20of%20their%20surroundings%2C%20whether%20that's%20while%20hiding%20in%20a%20box%20or%20behind%20vegetation%20in%20the%20Sahara.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f185f68d-40c6-41ac-b0cc-652b3c05e18e%5C%22%3E2.%20Cats%20are%20mini%20physicists%20at%20heart%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECats%20also%20tend%20to%20gravitate%20to%20boxes%20because%20those%20simple%20cardboard%20cubes%20can%20teach%20them%20about%20physics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20unique%20to%20boxes%2C%20though.%20Ever%20seen%20a%20cat%20knock%20over%20a%20glass%20with%20impunity%3F%20According%20to%20Roth%2C%20using%20objects%20to%20play%20can%20help%20cats%20understand%20the%20physics%20of%20the%20world%20around%20them%20%E2%80%94%20another%20vital%20piece%20of%20knowledge%20for%20predators.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20research%20even%20suggests%20cats%20understand%20the%20principle%20of%20cause%20and%20effect%3A%20One%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2016%2F06%2F160614114410.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2016%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%2030%20domestic%20cats%20found%20that%20the%20cats%20could%20understand%20when%20an%20object%20was%20present%20or%20not%2C%20purely%20by%20the%20presence%20or%20absence%20of%20sound.%20The%20researchers%20suggest%20this%20ability%20may%20be%20an%20important%20aspect%20of%20cat%20hunting%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22faa68c98-c54f-4b22-92d3-88e0f7460271%5C%22%3E3.%20Boxes%20may%20help%20with%20stress%20reduction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHiding%20away%20in%20a%20box%20may%20also%20help%20ease%20any%20stress%20your%20cat%20experiences.%20Common%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4157662%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estressors%20for%20pet%20cats%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EChanges%20in%20their%20environment%2C%20like%20moving%20house%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20addition%20of%20another%20family%20member%2C%20like%20a%20new%20partner%2C%20baby%2C%20or%20pet%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChanges%20in%20their%20routine%2C%20like%20a%20change%20in%20feeding%20schedule%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELack%20of%20enrichment%20and%20socialization%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.humanesociety.org%2Fnews%2Fkeeping-cats-stress-free%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECertain%20scents%20and%20sounds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20construction%20noises%2C%20scented%20candles%2C%20and%20perfumes%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIssues%20with%20their%20litter%20box%20setup%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS0168159114002366%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2014%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20boxes%20may%20help%20shelter%20cats%20better%20cope%20with%20stressors%20upon%20arrival.%20Researchers%20separated%2019%20shelter%20cats%20into%20two%20groups%2C%20one%20with%20access%20to%20a%20hiding%20box%20and%20the%20other%20without.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cats%20without%20a%20hiding%20box%20had%20higher%20stress%20scores%20and%20higher%20variance%20in%20stress%20scores%20over%20the%20two-week%20study%20period%2C%20compared%20to%20those%20who%20could%20sneak%20away%20into%20a%20box%20whenever%20they%20pleased.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENote%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20reducing%20your%20cat's%20stress%20levels%20may%20be%20as%20simple%20as%20eliminating%20stressors%20like%20loud%20noises%20or%20pungent%20scents.%20Offering%20plenty%20of%20opportunities%20for%20play%20and%20socialization%20can%20also%20help%20manage%20their%20ongoing%20stress.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d86d3e3-42c8-45bc-bf84-823acea6907b%5C%22%3E4.%20Boxes%20can%20satisfy%20their%20need%20to%20scratch%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECats%20seem%20to%20prefer%20textures%20they%20can%20sink%20their%20nails%20into%2C%20Roth%20says%2C%20which%20they%20can%20easily%20do%20with%20cardboard%20boxes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20again%2C%20this%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20predatory%20behaviors.%20Knowing%20how%20deep%2C%20how%20far%2C%20how%20fast%20to%20put%20those%20claws%20into%20something%20to%20either%20hold%20it%20still%20or%20dispatch%20it%20is%20the%20name%20of%20the%20game%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Roth%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuick%20tip%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBoxes%20may%20provide%20plenty%20of%20textural%20interest%2C%20but%20Roth%20also%20recommends%20offering%20a%20variety%20of%20textures%20for%20your%20cat%20to%20enjoy%2C%20such%20as%20blankets%20or%20stacks%20of%20paper%2C%20to%20find%20out%20what%20else%20satisfies%20their%20urges%20to%20scratch%20and%20shred.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20cat%20loves%20catnip%2C%20you%20can%20also%20try%20inexpensive%20cardboard%20scratchers%20infused%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fwhat-does-catnip-do-to-cats%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecatnip%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvcahospitals.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVCA%20Animal%20Hospitals%3C%2Fa%3E%20regional%20technician%20and%20assistant%20director%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvcahospitals.com%2Fpress-center%2Fvca-news%2Fjessica-sewell%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJessica%20Sewell%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff89e101-cece-4da6-a734-cb49f64d4532%5C%22%3E5.%20It's%20just%20part%20of%20their%20personality%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20humans%2C%20cats%20have%20different%20personalities%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20all%20cats%20will%20become%20fascinated%20with%20boxes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20cats%20will%20hide%20more%20than%20others%2C%20Roth%20says.%20If%20you%20find%20your%20cat%20hiding%20in%20a%20box%20more%20often%20than%20not%2C%20you%20may%20have%20a%20more%20introverted%20cat%2C%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20sudden%20changes%20in%20your%20cat's%20behavior%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20new%20tendency%20to%20seek%20out%20boxes%20and%20other%20hiding%20spots%20%E2%80%94%20could%20be%20a%20warning%20sign%20of%20a%20medical%20issue%2C%20though%2C%20Sewell%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e6358a39-e5da-44bd-ac82-ad8ff43be5d0%5C%22%3E6.%20Health%20issues%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20cat%20that%20suddenly%20seems%20withdrawn%20and%20takes%20refuge%20in%20small%20spaces%20could%20potentially%20have%20a%20health%20condition%2C%20such%20as%20diabetes%20or%20kidney%20disease.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20signs%20of%20an%20underlying%20health%20concern%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUnusual%20lethargy%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChanges%20in%20grooming%20habits%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENot%20eating%20or%20drinking%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUrinating%20or%20defecating%20inside%20hiding%20spaces%2C%20or%20anywhere%20else%20outside%20the%20litter%20box%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImportant%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIf%20you%20notice%20changes%20in%20your%20cat's%20behavior%20or%20they%20don't%20seem%20their%20usual%20self%2C%C2%A0%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20make%20an%20appointment%20with%20a%20vet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d78b689-60a3-4268-8a00-050d84a45da9%5C%22%3EPlaytime%20tips%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20think%20of%20cats%20as%20independent%20and%20aloof%2C%20but%20in%20reality%2C%20enrichment%20is%20just%20as%20important%20for%20your%20feline%20pals%20as%20it%20is%20for%20your%20canine%20companions%2C%20Sewell%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoth%20recommends%20taking%20advantage%20of%20a%20cat's%20predator-prey%20instinct%20to%20instigate%20playtime%20and%20add%20variety%20to%20their%20daily%20life.%20To%20engage%20your%20pet's%20natural%20prey%20drive%2C%20you%20might%20try%20some%20of%20the%20following%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlay%20hard%20to%20get%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Hide%20and%20let%20your%20cat%20come%20find%20you%2C%20or%20stash%20catnip%20toys%20around%20their%20favorite%20hiding%20spots.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFreeze%20up%20like%20a%20mouse%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20When%20actively%20playing%20with%20your%20cat%2C%20try%20freezing%20on%20the%20spot%20to%20engage%20their%20prey%20instinct.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ETry%20incorporating%20hunting%20games%20into%20their%20routine.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOne%20example%20of%20a%20hunting%20game%20involves%20making%20a%20trail%20of%20treats%20leading%20up%20to%20a%20hidden%20catnip%20toy%2C%20which%20allows%20cats%20to%20use%20senses%20other%20than%20their%20eyes%20and%20ears%2C%20Roth%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EMake%20their%20environment%20more%20interesting%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20Hang%20things%20on%20fishing%20poles%20or%20around%20hiding%20spots.%20This%20can%20help%20keep%20them%20entertained%20when%20you're%20not%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20what%20your%20cat%20finds%20interesting%20depends%20greatly%20on%20their%20personality%2C%20so%20you%20may%20need%20to%20experiment%20to%20find%20games%20and%20tactics%20that%20pique%20their%20curiosity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a121eaa4-0330-4e81-be56-c2e90d6d6c18%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBest%20cat%20toys%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%2214%20different%20cat%20toys%20including%20a%20plush%20beaver%2C%20small%20soccer%20balls%20and%20wire%20lying%20on%20a%20floor%20are%20some%20of%20the%20best%20cat%20toys%20in%202023%20we%20tested%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F61c3431517dae400125ad24f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221124%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EShoshi%20Parks%2FInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20something%20other%20than%20a%20box%20for%20your%20cat%20to%20play%20with%2C%20we%20rounded%20up%20some%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-toy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebest%20cat%20toys%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20mentall