r%20dog%20is%20eating%20is%20so%20fast.%20While%20hunger%20could%20be%20what's%20driving%20some%20dogs%20to%20hoover%20their%20meals%2C%20Dr.%20Carlo%20Siracusa%2C%20DVM%2C%20associate%20professor%20of%20clinical%20animal%20behavior%20and%20welfare%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%20School%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine%2C%20says%20that%20it's%20important%20to%20look%20at%20the%20whole%20picture.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20might%20be%20many%20reasons.%20One%20might%20be%20that%20you%20have%20more%20dogs%20in%20the%20house%20and%20they%20are%20not%20fed%20separately%2C%20and%20even%20if%20they%20are%2C%20there's%20not%20a%20physical%20barrier%20and%20they%20are%20afraid%20the%20other%20dog%20might%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Siracusa%20says.%20If%20you%20do%20select%20a%20slow%20feeder%20like%20the%20Outward%20Hound%2C%20he%20recommends%20watching%20your%20dog's%20body%20language%20to%20be%20sure%20they%20are%20enjoying%20the%20challenge%20the%20bowl%20presents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20bottom%20line%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Buster%2C%20the%20teal%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%20noopener%20nofollow%20nofollow%20nofollow%20nofollow%20nofollow%20sponsored%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%2F%3FamazonTrackingID%3Dbiipf_010820_outward-hound-feeder-review-20%26h%3Dab0885513279d7c2a0e3b1e43a6ac42394e99cfc6f3ba04d07872854e58bf40e%26postID%3D61b8efc7f2a36b1ac9f42b58%26postSlug%3Dguides%252Fpets%252Foutward-hound-fun-feeder-dog-bowl-review%26tags%3Dservice%253Acapi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fprf.hn%252Fclick%252Fcamref%253A1011l4Nww%252Fdestination%253Ahttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fwww.chewy.com%25252Fs%25253Fquery%25253DOutward%25252520Hound%25252520Fun%25252520Feeder%252526nav-submit-button%25253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOutward%20Hound%20Fun%20Feeder%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20hit.%20The%20dish%20held%20every%20meal%20he%20ate%20for%20the%20next%20two%20years%2C%20and%20when%20he%20passed%2